===Etymology===
Coined in 1813 by [[w:Sir Thomas Young|Sir Thomas Young]], from {{prefix|Indo|European}}, relating to the geographical extremes in [[India]] and [[Europe]] (which was valid before the discovery of [[Tocharian]] languages in the early 20th century).

===Proper noun===
{{en-proper noun}}

# A major [[language]] [[family]] which includes many of the native languages of [[Europe]], [[Western Asia]] and [[India]], with notable [[Indic]], [[Iranian]] and [[European]] sub-branches.
# [[Proto-Indo-European]]: the hypothetical parent language of the Indo-European language family.

